25Lm 3:21 This is what comes to mind, and therefore I have hope ?
25Lm 3:22 Because of the Lord's gracious love we are not consumed, since his compassions never end.
25Lm 3:23 They are new every morning - great is your faithfulness!
25Lm 3:24 "The Lord is all I have," says my soul, "Therefore I will trust in him."
25Lm 3:25 The Lord is good to those who wait for him, to the person who searches for him.
25Lm 3:26 It is good to hope and wait patiently for the Lord's salvation.
25Lm 3:27 It is good when a young man carries the yoke of discipline in his youth.
25Lm 3:28 He is to sit apart and remain silent, because the Lord has laid it upon him.
25Lm 3:29 Let him fall face down in the dust, so there may yet be hope.
25Lm 3:30 He will endure being slapped in the face, bringing him public disgrace. 
25Lm 3:31 Indeed, the Lord will not always reject us - 
25Lm 3:32 though he causes grief, his compassion abounds according to his gracious love.
25Lm 3:33 For he does not deliberately hurt or grieve human beings.
25Lm 3:34 When any of the prisoners of the earth are crushed underfoot,
25Lm 3:35 when a person's rights are perverted in defiance of the Most High.
25Lm 3:36 When a man is thwarted in his appeal does the Lord condone it - 
25Lm 3:37 Who can command, and it happens, without the Lord having ordered it - 
25Lm 3:38 Do not both good and evil things proceed from the mouth of the Most High - 
25Lm 3:39 Why should anyone living complain, any mortal, about being punished for sin - 
25Lm 3:40 Let us examine our lifestyles, putting them to the test, and turn back to the Lord.
25Lm 3:41 Let us lift up our hearts and our hands to God in heaven.41
25Lm 3:42 As for us, we have sinned and rebelled; but you have not pardoned us.
25Lm 3:43 Clothing yourself with anger, you pursued us. You killed without pity,
25Lm 3:44 You covered yourself with a cloud that prayer cannot pierce.
25Lm 3:45 You have reduced us to scum and garbage among the nations.
25Lm 3:46 All our enemies jeer at us with gaping mouths.
25Lm 3:47 Panic and pitfalls beset us, along with devastation and ruin.
25Lm 3:48 My eyes run with rivers of tears over the destruction of my cherished people.
25Lm 3:49 My tears pour down ceaselessly; I am far from relief
25Lm 3:50 until the Lord bends down to see from heaven.
25Lm 3:51 What I see grieves my soul because of all the young women of my city.
25Lm 3:52 My enemies hunted me like a bird, viciously and without justification.
25Lm 3:53 They dumped me alive into a pit, sealing me in with stone.
25Lm 3:54 Water closed over my head, and I said, "I'm a dead man."
25Lm 3:55 I called on your name, Lord, from the depths of the Pit,
25Lm 3:56 You heard my voice - don't close your ear to my sighs and cries.
25Lm 3:57 You drew near when I called out to you. You said, "Stop being afraid"358
25Lm 3:58 Lord, you have defended my cause; you have redeemed my life.
25Lm 3:59 Lord, you observed how I have been wronged; now make your ruling in my case.
25Lm 3:60 You examined their plans for vengeance, all of their plots against me.60
25Lm 3:61 Lord, you listened to their insults - 3all their plots against me,
25Lm 3:62 the whisperings of my opponents, their scheming against me all day long.
25Lm 3:63 Watch! Whether they sit down or stand up, they mock me with their songs.
25Lm 3:64 Pay them back, Lord, according to their actions.
25Lm 3:65 Give them an anguished heart; may your curse be upon them!
25Lm 3:66 Pursue them in your anger and destroy them from under the Lord's heaven.
25Lm 4:1 How tarnished the gold has become, the finest gold debased! Sacred stones have been scattered at every street corner.
25Lm 4:2 Though the precious people of Zion were like fine gold, how they are valued like clay vessels, the handiwork of a potter!
25Lm 4:3 Even wild animals nurse, suckling their young; but the women of my people are cruel, like ostriches in the wilderness.
25Lm 4:4 The nursing child's tongue cleaves to its palate from thirst.4Young children beg for bread, but no one gives them any.
25Lm 4:5 Those who enjoyed delicacies lie desolate in the streets. Those who were reared wearing purple scavenge in piles of trash.
25Lm 4:6 The guilt of my cherished people surpasses the sin of Sodom, which was overthrown in a moment, without a hand to help her.
25Lm 4:7 Her princes were purer than snow, whiter than milk. Their bodies were more ruddy than rubies, their beards like the color of precious stones.
25Lm 4:8 Now their faces are blacker than coal; they are unrecognized in the streets. Their skin clings to their bones; it has become dry like a stick.
25Lm 4:9 Those who die by the sword are better off9 than those who die from starvation, who slowly waste away like those pierced through for lack of food from the fields.
25Lm 4:10 With their own hands, compassionate women boil their own children - they become their food - when my beloved people were destroyed.
25Lm 4:11 The Lord has exhausted his wrath, pouring out his fierce anger. He kindled a fire in Zion, consuming its foundations.
25Lm 4:12 None of the kings of the earth would have believed, nor the world's inhabitants, that the adversary and the enemy could have breached the gates of Jerusalem.
25Lm 4:13 Due to the sins committed by her prophets, and the iniquities of her priests who shed in her midst, the blood of the righteous,
25Lm 4:14 people stagger around in the streets like the blind, defiled by blood unclean so that no one is able to touch their clothing.
25Lm 4:15 "Go away! Unclean!" they shouted at them. "Go away! Go away! Don't touch!" When they fled away and wandered, those among the nations decreed, "They cannot live here!"
25Lm 4:16 The Lord himself separated them; he will do nothing more for them. They did not respect their own priests; they did not honor their elders.
25Lm 4:17 Our eyes failed, searching in vain for hope; we kept watching and looking for a nation that would not help.
25Lm 4:18 Our steps were closely stalked, so we couldn't travel on our own streets. Our end is near, our days are over; indeed, our end has come.18
25Lm 4:19 Our pursuers were swifter than soaring eagles; they pursued us over the mountains, laying in wait for us in the wilderness.
25Lm 4:20 The Lord's anointed, the breath of our life, was captured in their pits. About him we had said, "Under his protection we will survive among the nations."
25Lm 4:21 Celebrate and rejoice, you women of Edom, who live in the land of Uz. But to you the cup also will pass - you will become drunk and stripped naked.21
25Lm 4:22 The punishment for your sin is complete, you women of Zion, and God will no longer exile you. He will punish your iniquity, you women of Edom, and he will expose your sins.
25Lm 5:1 Lord, remember what has happened to us. Pay attention, and look at our shame!
25Lm 5:2 Our inheritance has been turned over to strangers, and our homes to foreigners.
25Lm 5:3 We are now orphans - without fathers - and our mothers are like widows.
25Lm 5:4 We pay to drink our own water, and our own wood is sold to us at high price.
25Lm 5:5 Our pursuers breathe down our necks; we are weary, but there is no rest for us.6
25Lm 5:6 We made a deal with the Egyptians and the Assyrians for the price of food.
25Lm 5:7 Our ancestors sinned and no longer exist yet we continue to bear the consequences of their sin.
25Lm 5:8 Slaves rule over us, and no one delivers us from their control.8
25Lm 5:9 We risk our lives to obtain our food, facing death in the desert.
25Lm 5:10 Our skin blisters as from an oven, due to ravaging blasts of the famine.
25Lm 5:11 They have raped women in Zion, young women in the towns of Judah.
25Lm 5:12 Princes they have hung by their hands; elders they have disrespected.
25Lm 5:13 Our young men must grind grain with a millstone; our youths stumble under the weight of wood.
25Lm 5:14 Our elders have ceased ruling at the gate; our young men have abandoned their music.
25Lm 5:15 The joy of our hearts has ceased, and our dancing has turned into dirges.15
25Lm 5:16 The crown has fallen from our head - woe to us, because we have sinned!
25Lm 5:17 This is why our hearts faint, and why our eyes grow dim£º 
25Lm 5:18 Because Mount Zion is desolate; foxes roam around it.
25Lm 5:19 You, Lord, are forever - your throne endures from generation to generation.
25Lm 5:20 So why have you completely forgotten us, forsaking us for so long - 
25Lm 5:21 Restore us to yourself, Lord, so that we may return. Renew our days as before,
25Lm 5:22 unless you have utterly rejected us and are angry with us without limit.
