26Ezk 1:1 On the fifth day of the fourth month of the thirtieth year of the exile to Babylon, while I was among the captives on the bank of the Chebar River, heaven opened up and I saw visions from God.
26Ezk 1:2 On the fifth day of the month in the fifth year of King Jehoiachin's imprisonment in exile,
26Ezk 1:3 a message from the Lord came directly to Buzi's son Ezekiel, the priest, by the Chebar River in the land of the Chaldeans. The hand of the Lord rested upon him there.
26Ezk 1:4 I was amazed to see a wind storm blow in from the north, consisting of a massive cloud and fire that was flashing back and forth, surrounded by bright light. From deep within the cloud something was shining that appeared to have a color like bronze that had been placed in fire until it glowed.
26Ezk 1:5 Deep inside it, the likenesses of four living beings were visible. Their appearances were similar to human forms,
26Ezk 1:6 except that they each had four faces, four pairs of wings,
26Ezk 1:7 and straight legs. Their feet resembled calves' hooves, but they gleamed like polished bronze.
26Ezk 1:8 From under their wings there were human hands on their four sides. Now as to their four faces and four pairs of wings,
26Ezk 1:9 their pairs of wings overlapped each other. They moved in straight directions without turning their faces around as they moved.
26Ezk 1:10 The form of their faces was human, but each of the four also had the face of a lion to the right, the face of an ox to the left, and the face of an eagle behind them.
26Ezk 1:11 That's what their faces were like. Their wings spread out above and around them, one pair overlapping another, with one pair covering themselves.
26Ezk 1:12 Each moved in straight directions. Wherever they decided to go, they went without turning themselves.
26Ezk 1:13 Now, in the midst of the living beings there was something that appeared to glow like coals kindled by a fire, like torches that moved back and forth between the living beings. The fire was dazzling, and lightning flashed from the fire.
26Ezk 1:14 The living beings moved around, in appearance like lightning.
26Ezk 1:15 As I observed the living beings, I noticed one wheel on the earth beside each being - that is, for the four of them.
26Ezk 1:16 The appearance of their wheels and their construction details looked like gold-colored beryl. Each wheel was identical in form to the other four wheels, and their appearance and construction details were designed as if one wheel were within another.
26Ezk 1:17 Whenever the four moved, no matter which of four directions, they moved without turning around.1
26Ezk 1:18 Their wheel rims were ornate and terrifying. They were full of eyes that surrounded the four of them.
26Ezk 1:19 Whenever the living beings moved, the wheels moved, too. Whenever the living beings rose from the earth, the wheels rose also.
26Ezk 1:20 Whatever direction these spirits went, the wheels would be lifted up along with them, because the wheels were alive.
26Ezk 1:21 They moved around whenever they wanted to move around, and they stood still whenever they wanted to stand still; and whenever they rose from the earth, the wheels remained close beside them, because the wheels were also alive.
26Ezk 1:22 There was spread out over the heads of the living beings what looked like a canopy, in outward appearance resembling ice,
26Ezk 1:23 and underneath the canopy, their wings spread out straight over their heads toward each other. They each also had two wings with which they covered themselves, one wing covering its body on one side and one wing covering itself on the other side.
26Ezk 1:24 I also heard the sound of their wings, like the sound of roaring water, like the voice of the Almighty, or like a boisterous crowd within an army camp. Whenever they stopped flying, they lowered their wings.
26Ezk 1:25 A sound came from above the canopy that was spread out over their heads. Whenever they stood still, they lowered their wings.
26Ezk 1:26 From above the canopy, that was spread out over their heads there appeared to be something resembling a throne, in form resembling the appearance of sapphire. There was the likeness of the appearance of a human being seated on the likeness of the throne high above.
26Ezk 1:27 I noticed that from what appeared to look like his waist upward there was something that looked like metal that glowed as if it were immersed in fire. Below this there was something resembling fire, with a radiant light surrounding him.
26Ezk 1:28 The appearance of the radiant light resembled that of a rainbow shining in a cloud on a rainy day. This was what the appearance of the form of the glory of the Lord resembled. When I saw all of this, I fell flat on my face. Then I heard a voice speaking.
26Ezk 2:1 "Son of Man," the Lord said, "get up on your feet. I want to talk to you."
26Ezk 2:2 Even while he was speaking to me, the Spirit entered me, set me on my feet, and I listened to the voice that had been speaking to me.
26Ezk 2:3 "Son of Man, I'm sending you to that rebellious people, the Israelites, who have rebelled against me the same way their ancestors did. And they're still rebels to this very day!
26Ezk 2:4 They're stubborn and strong willed. I'm sending you to them to tell them what the Lord says.
26Ezk 2:5 Whether this rebellious group listens to you or not, at least they'll realize that a prophet had appeared in their midst!
26Ezk 2:6 "Now as for you, Son of Man, never be afraid of them or of anything they have to say, because being with them will be like settling down to live among briers, thornbushes, and scorpions! Don't be afraid of anything they have to say, and don't be awed by their appearance, since they are a rebellious group.
26Ezk 2:7 You are to tell hem whatever I have to say to them, whether they listen or not, since they are rebellious."
26Ezk 2:8 "Son of Man, you are to listen to what I tell you. You are never to be rebellious like they are£º a rebellious group. "Now, open your mouth and eat what I'm giving you¡¦"
26Ezk 2:9 As I watched, all of a sudden there was a hand being stretched out in my direction! And there was a scroll
26Ezk 2:10 being unrolled right in front of me! Written on both sides were lamentations, mourning, and cries of grief.
26Ezk 3:1 Then he told me, "Son of Man, eat! Eat what you see?this scroll?and then go talk to the house of Israel."
26Ezk 3:2 So I opened my mouth and he fed me the scroll.
26Ezk 3:3 Then he said to me, "Son of Man, feed your stomach and digest this scroll that I'm giving you." So I ate it, and it was like sweet honey in my mouth. 
26Ezk 3:4 Then he said to me, "Son of Man, go to the house of Israel and tell them what I have to say to them,
26Ezk 3:5 because you're not going to a people whose speech you cannot understand or whose language is difficult to speak. Instead, you're going to the house of Israel.
26Ezk 3:6 This isn't a large group of people whose speech is unintelligible to you or whose language is difficult for you to comprehend. Frankly, if I had sent you to that kind of people, they would certainly have listened to you!
26Ezk 3:7 But the house of Israel won't listen to you, since they weren't willing to listen to me. That's because the entire house of Israel is hard-headed and hard-hearted.
26Ezk 3:8 So pay attention! I'm going to make you just as obstinant and unyielding as they are.
26Ezk 3:9 I'm making you harder than flint?like diamond! So you are not to fear them or be intimidated by how they look at you, since they're a rebellious group."
26Ezk 3:10 Next, he told me, "Son of Man, take to heart every word that I'm telling you. Listen carefully,
26Ezk 3:11 then go immediately to the exiles; that is, to your people's descendants, and tell them, 'This is what the Lord God says¡¦' whether they listen or not."
26Ezk 3:12 Then the Spirit lifted me up and I heard a great earthquake behind me ans the glory of the Lord arose from his place,
26Ezk 3:13 accompanied by the sound of the wings of the living creatures gently touching each other and with the sound of the wheels emanating from the front, accompanied by a great earthquake. 
26Ezk 3:14 Then the Spirit lifted me up and carried me away. I went bitterly with an angry attitude as the hand of the Lord rested on me.
26Ezk 3:15 I came to the exiles at Tel-abib by the Chebar River and sat down among them for seven days, appalled.
26Ezk 3:16 At the end of the seven days, this message from the Lord came to me£º 
26Ezk 3:17 "Son of Man," he said, "I've appointed you to be a watchman over the house of Israel. Therefore when you hear a message that comes from me, you are to warn them for me.
26Ezk 3:18 "So when I say to the wicked, 'You're about to die,' if you don't warn him or instruct the wicked that his ways are wicked so he can live, that wicked man will die in his sin, but I will hold you responsible for his death.
26Ezk 3:19 If you warn the wicked, and he doesn't repent of his wickedness or of his wicked behavior, he'll die in his sin, but you will have saved your own life."
26Ezk 3:20 "When a righteous man abandons his righteousness to practice unrighteousness, I'll set a stumbling block before him. He'll die. If you don't warn him, he'll die in his sin and the righteous deeds that he had practiced won't be remembered, but you'll be held responsible for his death.
26Ezk 3:21 If you warn the righteous person, so that he doesn't commit sin, then he'll live, since he had been warned. And you will have saved your life." 
26Ezk 3:22 The hand of the Lord was upon me, and he said to me, "Get up, and go to the valley and, I'll speak with you there."
26Ezk 3:23 So I got up, went to the valley, and there was the glory of the Lord, standing there just like I had seen at the Kebar River. So I fell on my face.
26Ezk 3:24 The Spirit entered me, rested on me, caused me to stand on my feet, and then he spoke to me. This is what he had to say£º "Go and barricade yourself in your house.
26Ezk 3:25 Now pay attention! They're going to bind you with ropes, tying you up right in their midst, so you won't be able to circulate freely among them.
26Ezk 3:26 Meanwhile, I'll make tongue stick to the roof of your mouth so that you'll be mute and unable to reprove them, since they're a rebellious group.
26Ezk 3:27 But when I speak with you, I'll open your mouth so you can say to them, 'This is what Lord God says£º "As to those who will listen, 'Let them listen,' but as to those who refuse, 'Let them refuse,' since they're a rebellious group."'"
26Ezk 4:1 "And now Son of Man, you are to take a brick, set it in front of you, and inscribe on it the outline of the city?that is, Jerusalem.
26Ezk 4:2 You are to lay siege against it, build a rampart around it, set a bulwark against it, encircle it with a berm, set up camps against it, and place battering rams around it.
26Ezk 4:3 Then you are to take a flat iron plate and set it up as an iron wall between you and the city. "Next, you are to turn toward it, oppose it, and place it under siege, because you are to lay siege to it. All of this will serve as a sign to the house of Israel.
26Ezk 4:4 "Now as for you, you are to sleep on your left side, symbolically bearing the punishment of the house of Israel as you to count the days you'll be sleeping on your left side to bear the punishment of their sin.
26Ezk 4:5 I've assigned you to sleep this way for 390 days, representing the years they've been sinning, as you carry the punishment of the house of Israel.
26Ezk 4:6 When you have completed this, you are to sleep on your right and bear the iniquity of Judah for 40 days, each day representing one year that I've assigned for you. "After this, you are to turn toward the rampart of Jerusalem and oppose it with your bare arms, because I'm going to prophesy about it.
26Ezk 4:8 Look! I'll tie you up so that you're unable to turn from one side to the other until you've completed the duration of your siege."
26Ezk 4:9 "Furthermore, you are to take some wheat, barley, beans, lentils, millet, and spelt, and mix them together in one vessel. Then you are to make bread from these grains sufficient to supply you through the time during which you'll be sleeping on your side. You are to eat it for 390 days.
26Ezk 4:10 The food that you'll be eating is to consist of eight ounce portions for each day, consumed at regular intervals.
26Ezk 4:11 You are to measure a pint and a half of water each time you drink it.
26Ezk 4:12 You are to eat it as barley cakes and bake it right in front of them, using dried human dung for cooking fuel."
26Ezk 4:13 Then the Lord said, "This is how the Israelites will be eating unclean food among the nations, where I'll be sending them."
26Ezk 4:14 "Now, Lord God," I replied, "I've never been defiled, ever since I was young until now. I haven't eaten an animal that died of itself or was torn by beasts, and no unclean meat has ever entered my mouth!"
26Ezk 4:15 "Okay," he responded. "I'll allow you to substitute cow's dung for human dung. Cook your food over that."
26Ezk 4:16 He also told me, "Son of Man, look! I'm about to disrupt the source of bread in Jerusalem. As a result, they'll ration bread by weight in mounting terror and they'll ration drinking water in mounting horror.
26Ezk 4:17 Indeed, they'll need bread and water, but everyone will be panic-striken as they waste away in their iniquity."
26Ezk 5:1 "Now as for you, Son of Man, you are to go find a sharp sword and use it like a barber's razor. You are to cut your hair and beard. Then you are to take a weighing scale and divide your shaved hair into three parts.
26Ezk 5:2 You are to incinerate a third of it in the middle of thecity when you've finished your siege. Next, you are to take another third of it and beat it with your sword. Last, you are to scatter the remaining third to the wind, after which I'll unsheathe my sword and pursue them.
26Ezk 5:3 You are to preserve a few strands of hair and hide them in the folds of your garment.
26Ezk 5:4 Then you are to take a few strands, throw them in the fire, and incinerate them. A fire will proceed to the house of Israel from there."
26Ezk 5:5 "This is what the Lord God says, 'This is Jerusalem. I placed her as the center of the nations, with nations surrounding her.
26Ezk 5:6 But she rebelled against my ordinances and my statutes. She practiced more evil than all the nations and territories around her. They rejected my ordinances and didn't live by my statutes.'
26Ezk 5:7 "Therefore this is what the Lord God says£º 'Because you're more disrespectful than the nations that surround you, you didn't follow my statutes or follow my ordinances. You didn't even follow the ordinances of the surrounding nations!'
26Ezk 5:8 "Therefore this is what the Lord God says£º 'Watch out! I-that's right, even I-am against you. I'll carry out my sentence among you right in front of the nations.
26Ezk 5:9 In fact, I'm going to do what I've never done before and what I'll never again do, because of all of your loathsome behavior£º 
26Ezk 5:10 Fathers will eat their children in your midst. After this, your sons will eat their fathers as I carry out my sentence against you and scatter your survivors to the winds!'
26Ezk 5:11 "Therefore, as sure as I live," declares the Lord God, "because you've defiled my sanctuary with every loathsome thing and every abomination, I'll restrain myself, and my eyes won't show pity. Moreover, I won't have compassion.
26Ezk 5:12 A third of you will die by pestilence, starving because of the famine in your midst. Another third will die violently by the violence of war around you. The final third I'll scatter to the wind as I unsheathe my sword to pursue them.
26Ezk 5:13 "Only then will I'll stop being angry?my burning in anger. Then they'll know that I've spoken out in my arduous anger. Only then will my burning against them be exhausted.
26Ezk 5:14 I'm also going to turn you into a waste and an object of insult among the nations that surround you and in front of every person who passes by.
26Ezk 5:15 As a result, Jerusalem will become an insult, an object of taunt, an example of chastisement, and a useless waste to all the nations that surround you when I carry out my sentence against you in my anger, my burning rage, and my burning rebukes. I, the Lord, have spoken it.
26Ezk 5:16 I'll send arrows of severe famine in their direction, meant for destruction, which I'll shoot, intending to destroy them. I'll increase famines that will attack you and I'll disrupt your source of food.
26Ezk 5:17 "I'll send famine and wild beasts against you that will rob you of your children. Pestilence and bloodshed will devastate you when I'll declare war on you. I, the Lord, have spoken."
26Ezk 6:1 The Lord continued with his message to me.
26Ezk 6:2 "Son of Man,"he said, "turn your face to oppose the mountains of Israel and prophesy against them.
