26Ezk 6:10 Then they'll know that I am the Lord. I didn't declare this evil that's intended for them without a reason.'"
26Ezk 6:11 This is what the Lord God says£º "Clap your hands and stamp your feet! Say, 'Oh, no!' Because of all the detestable evil that's comes from Israel's house, they'll fall by the sword, famine, and pestilence.
26Ezk 6:12 The one who lives far away will die by pestilence and the one who is near will die violently. The survivors and their surveillance details will die by famine as I exhaust my rage against them.
26Ezk 6:13 You'll learn that I am the Lord, when the fatally wounded will be among their idols, around their altars, on every hill, on top of the mountains, under every luxuriant tree, and under every high foliage?every place where they've offered fragrant aromas to all their idols.
