26Ezk 16:2 "Son of Man, make known to Israel her detestable practices.
26Ezk 16:3 You are to declare, 'This is what the Lord God says to Jerusalem£º "Your birth place was the territory that belonged to the Canaanites. Your father was an Ammonite and your mother was a Hittite.
26Ezk 16:4 Now as to your birth, on the day you were born your umbilical cord wasn't cut. You weren't washed with water to clean you, and nobody rubbed you with salt. And it's certain that you weren't wrapped in strips of cloth.
26Ezk 16:5 Nobody pitied you to do any of these things for you, and nobody showed you any compassion. You were tossed outside on the ground, because you were detested from the day you were born. 
26Ezk 16:6 "'"When I passed by you, I saw you kicking around, covered in your own blood. That's when I said to you, 'Live!' - while you were wallowing in your blood. I commanded to you live, even as you lay there in your own blood.
26Ezk 16:7 I made you increase like sprouting grain in the field. As a result, you multiplied greatly. Eventually, you reached the age when young women start wearing jewlry. Your breasts were formed, your hair had grown, but you were still bare and naked."'"
26Ezk 16:8 "When I passed by you again, I looked at you, and noticed that it was your proper time for love. I spread my cloak over you to cover your nakedness. I made a solemn promise to you and entered into a covenant with you," declares the Lord God. "You belong to me.
26Ezk 16:9 I bathed you with water, rinsed your own blood from you, and anointed you with oil.
26Ezk 16:10 Then I covered you with embroidered clothing, clothed your feet with leather sandals, wrapped you with fine linen, and dressed you in silk.
26Ezk 16:11 I adorned you with jewels, placing bracelets on your hand and necklaces on your neck.
26Ezk 16:12 I put a ring in your nose, earrings in your ears, and a crown encrusted with jewels on your head.
26Ezk 16:13 You were adorned with gold, silver, clothing of fine linen, silk, and embroidery. You ate food made from finest flour, honey, and olive oil. You were exceedingly beautiful, attaining royal status.
26Ezk 16:14 Your fame spread throughout the nations because of your beauty. You were perfectly beauty due to my splendor with which I endowed you," declares the Lord God.8
26Ezk 16:15 "But you trusted in your beauty. You did what whores due, as a result of your fame. You passed out your sexual favors to anyone who passed by, giving yourself to anyone.
26Ezk 16:16 You took some of your clothes and made gaily-colored high places and prostituted yourself all around them-something which had never happened before nor will ever happen again.
26Ezk 16:17 "You also took your fine jewelry - including my gold and my silver that I had given you. Then you made for yourself male images and had sex with them!
26Ezk 16:18 You took your embroidered gowns and made clothes to cover them. Then you offered my olive oil and incense to them.
26Ezk 16:19 "Not only that, you took the food I gave you-my fine flour, olive oil, and honey which with I fed you, and you offered them to those gods in order to appease them. That's exactly what happened," says the Lord God.
26Ezk 16:20 "Then you took your sons and daughters whom you bore to me and sacrificed them for your idols to eat. As though your prostitutions were an insignificant thing,
26Ezk 16:21 you also slaughtered my sons and offered them to idols, incinerating them in fire.
26Ezk 16:22 Throughout all of your detestable practices and immorality, you never did remember your earlier life when you were bare, naked, and wallowing in your own blood."
26Ezk 16:23 "How terrible! How terrible it will be for all of your wickedness!" declares the Lord God.
26Ezk 16:24 "You built raised mounds and high places for yourself on every plaza.
26Ezk 16:25 At every street corner you made your beauty abhorrent when you parted your legs to anyone who passed by. By doing this you committed more and more immorality.
26Ezk 16:26 Then you committed immorality with your neighbors, the Egyptians, with perverted lust, and by doing so you increased your fornications and provoked me to anger.
26Ezk 16:27 "Therefore, look out! I've reached out to oppose you. I withdrew your rations and delivered you to those Philistine women who hate you. Even they were embarrassed at your wicked ways!
26Ezk 16:28 You committed fornication with the Assyrians, because you were never satisfied. You committed fornication with them, but you still weren't satisfied.
26Ezk 16:29 You increased your fornication with that land of the merchants, the Chaldeans. But you weren't satisfied even with these!
26Ezk 16:30 "How weak is your heart," declares the Lord God, "when you committed all of these deeds, the acts of an imperious whore!
26Ezk 16:31 When you built your mound on every street corner and constructed your high place at every plaza, you weren't like a common prostitute, in that you've insulted the wages of a prostitute
26Ezk 16:32 who commits adultery, preferring a stranger over her husband!
26Ezk 16:33 "All prostitutes receive gifts, but you give your gifts to all your lovers then bribe them to come to you from every where for your favors.
26Ezk 16:34 You're different from other women in your fornications - no one can duplicate you in how you commit fornication. After all, you pay fees, but no fee is given to you. You're certainly different!"
26Ezk 16:35 "Therefore listen to this message from the Lord, you whore!
26Ezk 16:36 This is what the Lord God says£º 'Because your lust has been poured out and your nakedness has been uncovered by your acts of fornication with your lovers, and because of all your detestable idols and the blood of your sons, whom you offered to them,
26Ezk 16:37 therefore, watch out! I'm about to gather all your lovers from whom you've received your pleasure, everyone whom you've loved, and those whom you've hated. I'll gather them together to oppose you from every side, and they'll uncover your nakedness in their presence. Then they'll see your completely naked.
26Ezk 16:38 I'll judge you with the same standards by which I issue verdicts against a woman who commits adultery and murder. I'll avenge the blood you've shed with impassioned wrath.37
26Ezk 16:39 "I'll also deliver you into their control, and they'll break down your mounds, tear down your high places, strip off your clothes, remove your fine jewels, and then they'll leave you stark naked!
26Ezk 16:40 They'll bring a mob against you to stone you to death with stones and cut you into pieces with their swords.
26Ezk 16:41 Then they'll burn your houses and execute judgment against you in the sight of many women. "That's how I'll cause you stop your prostitution so you won't pay any prostitute's fees anymore.
26Ezk 16:42 I'll cause my anger against you to stop and I'll turn aside my jealous disposition from you. I'll be calm and not be indignant any more.
26Ezk 16:43 Because you didn't remember the time when you were young, but instead you provoked me to anger because of all these things, watch out! I'm going to bring your behavior back to you," declares the Lord God. "Didn't you do this wickedness, along with all your detestable practices?
26Ezk 16:44 "Now, everyone who likes proverbs will say proverb about you, 'Like mother, like daughter.'
26Ezk 16:45 You're the daughter of your mother, who loathed her husband and children. You're the sister of your sisters, who loathed their husbands and children. "Your mother was a Hittite and your father was an Amorite.
26Ezk 16:46 Your elder sister was Samaria. She and her daughters lived in the north, while your younger sister who lived in the south with her daughters was Sodom.
26Ezk 16:47 It wasn't just that you lived like they did and committed their detestable practices, but in just a little while your behavior led you to become more corrupt than they were!"
26Ezk 16:48 "As I live," declares the Lord God, "your sister Sodom and her daughters didn't do what you and your daughters have done.
26Ezk 16:49 Look! This was the sin of your sister Sodom and her daughters£º Pride, too much food, undisturbed peace, and failure to help the poor and needy.
26Ezk 16:50 In their arrogance, they committed detestable practices in my presence, so when I saw it, I removed them.
26Ezk 16:51 Samaria didn't commit half of your sins-you practiced more detestable practices deeds than they did! You've caused your sister to be more righteous than you, because of the detestable practices that you've committed.
26Ezk 16:52 So now, bear your own shame as you mediate for your sisters. The sins that you've committed, are more detestable than theirs. That makes them more righteous than you. Indeed, be ashamed and bear your reproach, because you've made your sisters to be more righteous than you."
26Ezk 16:53 "I'll reverse their captivity-that is, the captivity of Sodom and her daughters, along with the captivity of Samaria and her daughters and the captivity of your captives among them.
26Ezk 16:54 But you'll continue to bear your own reproach and be humiliated for everything that you've done. You'll be a comfort to them.
26Ezk 16:55 Your sister Sodom and her daughters will be restored to their former status. Samaria and her daughters will be restored to their former status. Then you and your daughters will be restored to your former status.
26Ezk 16:56 "When you were being so arrogant, you never once mentioned your sister Sodom
26Ezk 16:57 before your wickedness was uncovered. Now you've become an object of derision to the inhabitants of Aram and its environs, including the Philistines - all those around you who despise you.
26Ezk 16:58 You are to bear the punishment of your wickedness and detestable practices," declares the Lord,
26Ezk 16:59 "since the Lord God says, 'I'll deal with you according to what you've done, when you despised your oath by breaking the covenant.
26Ezk 16:60 "'Meanwhile, as for me, I'll remember my covenant with you from when you were young, because I'll establish an eternal covenant with you.
26Ezk 16:61 Then you'll remember your behavior and be ashamed when you receive your sisters-your elder sister and your younger sister. I'll give them to you as daughters, but not on account of my covenant with you.
26Ezk 16:62 I'll establish my covenant with you, and then you'll know that I am the Lord.
26Ezk 16:63 Then you will remember, be ashamed, and you won't open your mouth any more due to humiliation when I shall have made atonement for you for everything that you've done,' declares the Lord God."
26Ezk 17:1 This message came to me from the Lord£º 
26Ezk 17:2 "Son of Man, propound a riddle and relate a parable to Israel's house.
26Ezk 17:3 Tell them, 'This is what the Lord God says, "A massive eagle with gigantic wings, long pinions, and full, multi-colored plumage came to Lebanon and took away the top of the cedar.
26Ezk 17:4 He plucked off the top of its shoot, brought it to a land of merchants, and set it down in a city full of traders.
26Ezk 17:5 Then the eagle took a seed from the land and planted it on fertile ground. He planted it like a willow tree next to abundant waters.
26Ezk 17:6 It flourished and became a spreading vine of low stature. Its branches turned toward him, and its roots spread under him to become a vine that put out shoots and spread out its branches.
26Ezk 17:7 "All of a sudden, there was another eagle with gigantic wings and thick plumage. The vine stretched its roots hungrily toward him and spread its branches out to him in order to be watered on the terraces where it was planted.
26Ezk 17:8 It was transplanted into good soil near abundant water, and it produced branches and bore fruit, becoming a magnificent vine."
26Ezk 17:9 "Tell them, 'This is what the Lord God says, "Will it prosper?Won't it pull up its roots, and be stripped bare so that all of its fresh foliage dries up?It won't be by great strength or great army that its roots will be pulled out.
26Ezk 17:10 Look! Because it's a transplanted vine, won't it wither when the east wind strikes against it?It will surely wither in the terraces where it had started to sprout."'"
26Ezk 17:11 This message came to me from the Lord£º 
26Ezk 17:12 "Tell my rebellious house, 'Don't you know what these things mean?Look! The king of Babylon came to Jerusalem, captured her king and princes, and took them with him to Babylon.
26Ezk 17:13 Then he took one of the royal descendants, made a covenant with him, and put him under an oath of loyalty. He took the leaders of the land captive
26Ezk 17:14 in order to humiliate the kingdom so it wouldn't be able to come back into power, but would still be able to continue as long as he keeps his covenant.
26Ezk 17:15 But he rebelled against the king of Babylon by sending his messengers to Egypt to obtain horses and a large army. Will he succeed?Or will the one who did this escape?Will he break the covenant, but still yet anyway?"
26Ezk 17:16 "As long as I live," declares the Lord God, in Babylon, "that place where the king has enthroned him, whose oath he despised so as to break his covenant, he'll die with him.
26Ezk 17:17 Pharaoh, with his massive army and large batallions won't protect him when mounds and siege walls are built to destroy many people.
26Ezk 17:18 He despised the oath he had made and broke the covenant. Look! Because he willingly submitted, yet he has done all these things, he won't escape. 
26Ezk 17:19 "Therefore, this is what the Lord God says, 'As long as I live, because he despised my oath and broke my covenant, I'll bring it upon his head.
26Ezk 17:20 I'll spread my net over him so that he'll be caught in my snare. I'll bring him to Babylon and enter into judgment with him there for his treacherous acts that he committed against me.
26Ezk 17:21 The fugitives of his troops will die by the sword, and the survivors will be scattered to the four winds. Then you'll know that I, the Lord, have spoken.'"
26Ezk 17:22 "This is what the Lord God says, 'I'm also going to take a shoot from the top of a cedar and plant it. I'll pluck off its delicate twigs and transplant it on a high and lofty mountain.
26Ezk 17:23 I'll transplant it on Israel's land, and it will bring out branches, bear fruit, and become a majestic cedar. All sorts of birds will rest under it, and they'll settle down in the shade of its branches.
26Ezk 17:24 Then all the trees of the fields will know that I, the Lord, bring down the lofty tree and exalt the lowly tree. I dry up the green tree and cause the dry tree to bud. I the Lord have spoken this, and I will fulfill it.'"
26Ezk 18:1 This message came to me from the Lord£º 
26Ezk 18:2 "Why do you cite this proverb when you talk about Israel's land£º 'The fathers eat sour grapes but it's their chidlren's teeth that have lost their sharpness.'
26Ezk 18:3 As long as I live," declares the Lord, "you won't use this proverb about Israel anymore.
26Ezk 18:4 Look! Every living soul belongs to me-the father's as well as the son's. So pay attention! The person who keeps on sinning is going to die."
26Ezk 18:5 "If a person is righteous, and practices what's lawful and right,
26Ezk 18:6 if he doesn't eat at mountain shrines, and doesn't look to the idols that have been erected in Israel's house, if he doesn't defile his neighbor's wife or approach a woman during her time of menstrul separation,
26Ezk 18:7 if he doesn't oppress anyone, but instead returns the debtor's security for his debt, if he doesn't rob anyone, but instead shares his food to the hungry and covers the naked with clothing,
26Ezk 18:8 if he doesn't lend with usury or exact interest, but instead refuses to participate in what is unjust, if he executes true justice between man and man,
26Ezk 18:9 if he lives his life in my statutes and keeps my ordinances by practicing what's true, then he's righteous and will certainly live," declares the Lord God.
26Ezk 18:10 "Now suppose that person produces a son who's violent, a murderer, and practices any of these things,
26Ezk 18:11 even though the father hasn't done any of these things. The son who eats at mountain shrines, defiles his neighbor's wife,
26Ezk 18:12 oppresses the afflicted and the poor, robs others, doesn't return security for a debt, looks to idols does detestable things,
26Ezk 18:13 loans with usury, and exacts interest, will he live?He certainly will not! He has done all these detestable practices. He will certainly die, and his guilt will be his own fault."
26Ezk 18:14 "Noow suppose that he produced a son who practiced all of his father's sins, but then that son began to fear me and stopped doing all of these things.
26Ezk 18:15 That is, suppose he doesn't eat at the mountain shrines, doesn't look to the idols of Israel's house, doesn't defile his neighbor's wife,
26Ezk 18:16 doesn't oppress anyone, doesn't take possession of a debtor's pledge, or doesn't steal, but instead shares his food with the hungry and covers the naked with clothing,
26Ezk 18:17 doesn't refuse to help the afflicted, or refuses to loan with usury or exact interest, but instead carries my ordinances and lives his life consistent with my statutes. He won't die because of his father's sin, will he?No! He'll certainly live.
26Ezk 18:18 As for his father, watch out! If he wrongfully oppressed or robbed his brother and did what wasn't good among his people, he'll die in his own sin."15
26Ezk 18:19 "Yet you keep asking, 'Why wouldn't the son bear the punishment of his father's sin? Because the son has done what was lawful and right, and has kept all my statutes and obeyed them, he's certainly going to live.
26Ezk 18:20 The soul who sins dies. The son won't bear the punishment of his father's sin and the father won't bear the punishment of his son's sin. The righteous deeds of the righteous will be attributed to him, while the wicked deeds of the wicked will be charged against him.
26Ezk 18:21 But if the wicked turns from all his sins, which he did and keeps my statutes, then he'll live. He won't die.
26Ezk 18:22 None of the transgressions that he had committed, will be remembered against him. Because of the righteous deeds that he had done, he'll live.
26Ezk 18:23 "Do I take delight in the death of the wicked? asks the Lord God. "Shouldn't I rather delight when he turns from his wicked ways and lives - 
26Ezk 18:24 But when the righteous person abandons his righteous deeds and commits evil, detestable practices, as wicked people do, will he live?None of the righteous acts that he had done will be remembered. With his unfaithfulness where he had acted treacherously and his sins, which he had committed, he'll die in them."
26Ezk 18:25 "Yet you keep saying, 'The Lord isn't being consistent with his standards.' Pay attention, you house of Israel£º Is my behavior really inconsistent with my standards?Isn't it your behavior that isn't just - 
26Ezk 18:26 "When a righteous person turns from his righteous deeds and does evil, he'll die because of that evil. He'll die because of his unrighteous acts that he committed.
26Ezk 18:27 When a wicked person abandons his wicked behavior that he had committed and does what's just and right, he'll be enabled to live.
26Ezk 18:28 Because he considered his transgression and turned away from all of what he had committed, he'll certainly surely live and not die.
26Ezk 18:29 Yet Israel's house keeps saying, 'The Lord isn't being consistent with his standards. Isn't my behavior really inconsistent with my standards?Is it not your behavior that is inconsistent with my standards?
26Ezk 18:30 "Therefore, Israel, I'm going to judge you according to the behavior of each and every one of you," declares the Lord God. "So repent and turn from all your sins so that sin won't keep on being a stumbling block for you.
26Ezk 18:31 Throw away all of your transgressions, the deeds by which you've rebelled, and then make for yourselves a new heart and a new spirit. Why should you die, you house of Israel - 
26Ezk 18:32 I don't take pleasure in the death of anyone who dies," declares the Lord. "So repent, so you may live!"
26Ezk 19:1 "Now as for you, publish this mourning psalm about Israel's leaders.
26Ezk 19:2 Tell them£º 'What a lioness your mother was among lions! She reared her cubs in the midst of fierce young males.
26Ezk 19:3 She raised one cub in particular, teaching that fierce lion to become a hunter-prowler?to eat human beings.
26Ezk 19:4 The nations heard about him. He had become caught in their trap. They brought him with hooks to the land of Egypt.
26Ezk 19:5 When she learned that her plans had been frustrated and that her hopes were dashed, she took another of her cubs and turned him into a fierce lion.
26Ezk 19:6 He prowled around among the lions, became a strong, young lion, and learned to become a hunter-prowler?to eat human beings.
26Ezk 19:7 He raped the women, devastating their towns. The land was made desolate, and all the while the land was filled with the sound of his roaring.
26Ezk 19:8 The surrounding nations attacked. They tossed their net over him, and he was caught in their trap.
26Ezk 19:9 The imprisoned him in a cage with hooks and brought him to the king of Babel. Then they placed him in their dungeon where his voice would no longer be heard on the mountains of Israel.
26Ezk 19:10 'Your mother was like a vine entwining a pomegranate, planted by water, full of fruit, and full of branches because it had been watered generously.
26Ezk 19:11 Strong were its boughs, suitable for use in the scepter of a ruler. It reached to the clouds, noticeable because of its height and its abundant branches.
26Ezk 19:12 Yet in anger it was uprooted and cast down to the earth. An east wind dessicated its fruit; its strong branches broke off and withered, and a fire consumed them.
26Ezk 19:13 Now it is planted in the desert, in a dry and thirsty land!
26Ezk 19:14 Fire had burned through its branches, consuming its shoots and fruits. No strong branches remain in it, and there is no scepter to rule!' "This is a lamentation, and it is to be used in mourning."
26Ezk 20:1 On the seventh year, on the tenth day of the fifth month, men came from the elders of Israel to seek the Lord. They sat down in front of me.
26Ezk 20:2 "Son of Man," the Lord told me,
26Ezk 20:3 "Tell the elders of Israel, 'This is what the Lord God asks, "Did you come to inquire of me?As long as I live, I won't let myself be sought by you," declares the Lord God.'
26Ezk 20:4 "Will you judge them?Son of Man, will you indeed judge them?Teach them about the detestable practices that their ancestors did.
26Ezk 20:5 Tell them, 'This is what the Lord God says, "The day I chose Israel, when I made my commitment to the descendants of Jacob's house, I revealed myself to them in the land of Egypt and I made my promise to them with the words 'I am the Lord your God.'
26Ezk 20:6 That day I promised to bring them out of the land of Egypt to the land that I had explored for them - a land flowing with milk and honey. It's the most beautiful of all lands.
26Ezk 20:7 Then I said to them, 'Each of you are to abandon your detestable practices. You are not to defile yourselves with Egypt's idols. I am the Lord your God.'"
26Ezk 20:8 "But they rebelled against me and weren't willing to obey me. None of them abandoned their detestable practices or their Egyptian idols. So I said, 'I'll pour out my anger and spend my fury against them in the midst of the land of Egypt.'
26Ezk 20:9 I did this so my reputation might not be tarnished among the nations where they were living, among whom I made myself known in their presence when I brought them out of the land of Egypt.
26Ezk 20:10 I brought them out of the land of Egypt to bring them to the wilderness
26Ezk 20:11 where I gave them my statutes and revealed my ordinances to them, which if a person observes, he'll live by them.
26Ezk 20:12 Also, I instituted my Sabbath for them as a sign between me and them, so they would know that I am the Lord, who has set them apart."
26Ezk 20:13 "But the house of Israel rebelled against me in the wilderness. They didn't live by my statutes. They despised my ordinances, which if a person observes, he'll live by them. They greatly profaned my Sabbaths. So I said I would pour out my anger on them and bring them to an end in the wilderness.
26Ezk 20:14 I did this so my reputation wouldn't be tarnished among the nations in whose presence I had brought them out.
26Ezk 20:15 "Moreover, I solemnly swore to them in the wilderness that I wouldn't bring them to the land that I had given them?a land flowing with milk and honey, the most beautiful of all lands - 16because they kept on rejecting my ordinances. They didn't live life consistent with my statutes, they profaned my Sabbaths, and their hearts followed their idols.
26Ezk 20:17 Even then, I looked on them with compassion and didn't completely destroy them in the wilderness.
26Ezk 20:18 I told their children in the wilderness, 'You are not to follow the statutes of your ancestors, observe their ordinances, or be defiled by their idols.
26Ezk 20:19 I am the Lord your God. You are to follow my statutes, observe my ordinances, and keep them.
26Ezk 20:20 You are to make my Sabbaths sacred, and you are to let them serve as a sign between you and me, so that you may know that I am the Lord your God."
26Ezk 20:21 "But they rebelled against me. They didn't live according to my statutes, observe my ordinances, or practice them, by which a person will live. They also kept profaning my Sabbaths. So I said that I was going to pour out my anger on them and in my anger bring a complete end to them in the wilderness.
26Ezk 20:22 But I withdrew my decision so my reputation wouldn't be tarnished among the nations before whose eyes I brought them out.
26Ezk 20:23 "Futhermore, I solemnly swore in the wilderness to disperse them among the nations and scatter them to other lands
26Ezk 20:24 because they didn't observe my ordinances. Instead, they rejected my statutes, profaned my Sabbaths, and worshipped their ancestors' idols.
26Ezk 20:25 So I gave them statutes that weren't good and ordinances by which they could not live.
26Ezk 20:26 I made them unclean because of their offerings, so they made all their firstborn to pass through the fire, so that I could make them appalled. Then they'll know that I am the Lord."
26Ezk 20:27 "Therefore, Son of Man, you are to speak to the children of Israel and tell them, "This is what the Lord God says£º 'Your ancestors also blasphemed me in their treacherous behavior against me.
26Ezk 20:28 I brought them to the land that I had promised to give them. But whenever they saw any high hill and or any leafy tree, they slaughtered their sacrifices there and presented their offerings that provoked my anger. There they presented their pleasing aromas and poured out their drink offering.
26Ezk 20:29 So I asked them, "What is the high place to which you're going? That's why the name of the place has been called Bamah to this day.'"
26Ezk 20:30 "Therefore you are to say to Israel's house, "This is what the Lord God says£º 'Will you defile yourselves like your ancestors did by acting as a prostitute, consistent with their horrible deeds - 
26Ezk 20:31 When you present your gifts and make your sons pass through the fire, you continue to defile yourselves with your idols to this day. Should I be inquired of by you, you house of Israel?As I live,' declares the Lord, 'I certainly won't be inquired of by you.'
26Ezk 20:32 The thing that you're imagining is never going to happen, since you're thinking, 'We'll be like the nations, like the clans of other lands who serve gods made from wood and stone.'"
26Ezk 20:33 "As I live," declares the Lord God, "with my powerful hand and outstreched arm, along with my wrath poured out, I'll reign as king over you.
26Ezk 20:34 I'll bring you out from the peoples and gather you from the lands where you were scattered. With a powerful hand, with an outstretched arm, and with wrath poured out
26Ezk 20:35 I'll bring you into the wilderness of the peoples. I'll enter into judgment with you there face to face.
26Ezk 20:36 Just as I've entered into judgment with your ancestors in the wilderness in the land of Egypt, so I'll enter into judgment with you," declares the Lord.
26Ezk 20:37 "I'll cause you to pass under the rod until I shall have brought you into the bond of the covenant.
26Ezk 20:38 I'll eliminate the rebels among you, along with those who are transgressing against me. I'll bring them out of the land where you've lived, but they won't be able to enter the land of Israel. Then you'll know that I am the Lord."
26Ezk 20:39 "And now, you house of Israel, this is what the Lord God says, 'Go ahead and serve your idols, and thereafter, but later you'll listen to me, and you won't profane my sacred name again by your offerings and idols."
26Ezk 20:40 "For on my holy mountain, on Israel's high mountains," declares the Lord God, "the whole of Israel's house, all of it, will serve me there in the land. I'll accept them there. And there I'll demand your offerings, the first fruits of your portions of all your sacred things.
26Ezk 20:41 "When I shall have brought you from among the people and have gathered you from the lands where you were scattered, I'll accept you as a pleasing aroma. I'll reveal my holiness among you, and the entire world will see it.
26Ezk 20:42 Then you'll know that I, the Lord, brought you to the land of Israel, to the land that I promised to give to your ancestors.
26Ezk 20:43 You'll remember all your practices and evils deeds by which you've become defiled. You'll loathe yourselves in your own sight because of all the evil things you've done.
26Ezk 20:44 Then you'll know that I am the Lord, when I shall have dealt with you for the benefit of my own reputation and not according to your evil attitudes or corrupt practices, you house of Israel," declares the Lord God."
26Ezk 20:45 This message came to me from the Lord£º 
26Ezk 20:46 "Son of Man, turn to the south and oppose it, talking toward the south.
26Ezk 20:47 Prophesy against the forest of the Negev, 'Listen to the word of the Lord. This is what the Lord God says£º 'Look out! I'm about to kindle a fire against you that will devour tree?whether green or dry?that lives in you. This powerful flame will not be extinguishable, and the entire surface from so uth to north will be scorched by it.
26Ezk 20:48 Then everyone will see that I, the Lord, have kindled it, because it won't be extinguished."
26Ezk 20:49 Then I said, "O Lord God! They're saying about me, 'Isn't he one to propound parables?" 
26Ezk 21:1 This message came to me from the Lord£º 
26Ezk 21:2 "Son of Man, look toward Jerusalem, preach against its sanctuaries, and prophesy against Israel's land.
26Ezk 21:3 Declare to Israel's land, 'This is what the Lord says£º "Watch out! I'm against you! I'm going to unsheathe my sword to kill both the righteous and the wicked among you.
