26Ezk 41:20 from the ground to above the doorway, as well as on the walls of the main sanctuary.
26Ezk 41:21 The door posts of the main sanctuary were square. Each door post was identical in appearance to any other.
26Ezk 41:22 The altar was made of wood, three cubits high and two cubits long. Its corners, base, and wides were of wood. He told me, "This table stands in the Lord's presence."
26Ezk 41:23 The nave and the sanctuary each were equipped with double doors.
26Ezk 41:24 Each door had two sections mounted on hinges, for a total of two sections for one door and two sections for the other.
26Ezk 41:25 The doors of the nave had carvings engraved on them, consisting of cherubim and palm trees identical to those on the walls. The front of the exterior porch was equipped with a wooden threshold.
26Ezk 41:26 Shielded windows and palm trees were visible on both sides; that is, on the sides of the porch, the side chambers of the temple, and on its thresholds.
26Ezk 42:1 Then he brought me to the outer, north-facing courtyard into the chamber that stood opposite the structure that was facing north.
