26Ezk 42:17 the north side at 500 reeds, according to the length of the measuring stick,
26Ezk 42:18 the south side at 500 reeds, according to the length of the measuring stick,
26Ezk 42:19 and the west side at 500 reeds, according to the length of the measuring stick.
26Ezk 42:20 He measured a wall that encompassed all four sides, 500 hundred long and 500 wide, dividing between the sacred and the common.
26Ezk 43:1 Next, he brought me to the east facing gate,
26Ezk 43:2 and the glory of the God of Israel was coming from the east. His voice sounded like roaring water, and the land shimmered from his glory.
26Ezk 43:3 His appearance in the vision that I was having was similar to what I observed in the vision where he had come to destroy the city, and also like the visions that I saw by the Chebar River. I fell flat on my face
26Ezk 43:4 while the glory of the Lord entered the tample by way of the east-facing gate.
26Ezk 43:5 Just then, the Spirit lifted me up and carried me into the inner courtyard, where the glory of the Lord was filling the temple!
26Ezk 43:6 I heard someone speaking to me from the temple, and a man appeared, standing beside me!
26Ezk 43:7 "Son of Man," the Lord God told me, "This is where my throne is, where I place the soles of my feet, and where I will live among the Israelites forever. The house of Israel will no longer defile my holy name-neither they nor their kings - by their unfaithfulness, by the lifeless idols of their kings on their funeral mounds,
26Ezk 43:8 by their setting up their threshold too close to my threshold and their door post too close to my door post, with a wall between me and them. After all, they have defiled my holy name by their loathsome things that they did, so I devoured them in my anger.
26Ezk 43:9 But now let them send their unfaithfulness and lifeless idols of their kings far away from me, and I will live among them forever."
26Ezk 43:10 "And now, Son of Man, describe the temple to the house of Israel. They will be ashamed because of their sin. They will measure its pattern.
26Ezk 43:11 If they are ashamed of everything that they've done, you are to reveal to them the design of the temple, its structure, its exits and entrances, its plans, its ordinances, and all of its regulations. Write it down where they can see it and remember all of its designs and regulations, so they will implement them.
26Ezk 43:12 This is to be the regulation for the temple£º the entire area on top of the mountain is to be considered wholly consecrated. This is to be the law of the temple."11
26Ezk 43:13 "Here are the measurements of the altar in cubits that were a cubit and a handbreadth long£º its base is a cubit long and a cubit wide, and its border around the edge at one handbreadth is to be the height of the altar.
26Ezk 43:14 From the base on the ground to its lower edge is to be two cubits, with its width to be one cubit. From the lesser ledge to the larger edge is to be four cubits. Its width is to be one cubit.13
26Ezk 43:15 "The hearth is to be four cubits high, and four horns are to extend upwards from the hearth.
26Ezk 43:16 "The hearth is to be twelve cubits long and twelve cubits wide; that is, it will be a four-sided square.
26Ezk 43:17 It is to have a ledge fourteen cubits long by fourteen cubits wide around the four sides. Its border is to be half a cubit and its base is to be a cubit all around, with its steps facing east."
26Ezk 43:18 Then he said to me, "This is what the Lord God says£º 'These are the regulations for the altar, starting the day that it is constructed for presenting burnt offerings and sprinkling blood.
26Ezk 43:19 You are to present to the Levitical priests, Zadok's descendants, who will approach me to serve me, a young bull for a sin offering,' declares the Lord God.
26Ezk 43:20 'You are to take some of its blood and put it on the four horns of the altar, on its four corners of the ledge, and on the border that surrounds it, thus cleansing it and making an atonement for it.
26Ezk 43:21 You are also to present a bull for a sin offering, incincerating it in the appointed place at the temple, outside the sanctuary.
26Ezk 43:22 "The second day following commencement of offerings, you are to offer a male goat without defect for a sin offering to cleanse the altar the same way they cleansed it with the bull.
26Ezk 43:23 After you've finished the cleansing, you are to present a young bull without defect and a ram from the flock without defect.
26Ezk 43:24 You are to present them in the Lord's presence, and the priests are to throw salt on them and then present them as a burnt offering to the Lord.
26Ezk 43:25 "Every day for a week, you are to prepare a goat for a sin offering, a young bull, and a ram from the flock, each without defect.
26Ezk 43:26 For a seven day period they are to make atonement for the altar, purifying it and consecrating it.
