26Ezk 44:1 Then the Lord God brought me back by way of the east-facing outer gate of the sanctuary. But it was shut. 
26Ezk 44:2 The Lord said to me, "This gate is to remain shut. It will not be opened. No man is to enter in by it, because the Lord God of Israel entered in by it, so it is to remain shut.
26Ezk 44:3 The Regent Prince will be seated there, as Regent Prince, and will dine in the Lord's presence, entering by way of the portico of the gate and exiting by the same way."
26Ezk 44:4 Then he brought me by way of the north-facing gate to the front of the temple. As I looked, the glory of the Lord filled the Lord's temple, and I fell flat on my face!
26Ezk 44:5 Then the Lord told me, "Son of Man, watch carefully, listen closely, and remember everything I'm going to be telling you about all the statutes pertaining to the Lord's temple and all of its laws. Pay careful attention to the entrance to the temple, along with all of the exits to the sanctuary."
26Ezk 44:6 "You are to tell the Resistance-that is, the house of Israel, 'This is what the Lord God says£º "I've had enough of all of your loathsome behavior, you house of Israel!
26Ezk 44:7 You kept on bringing in foreigners, those who were both uncircumcised in heart and flesh, to profane my sanctuary by being inside my temple, and by doing so you've emptied my covenant, all the while offering my food - the fat and the blood - in addition to all of your other loathsome things.
26Ezk 44:8 Furthermore, you haven't observed the requirements of my holy things. Instead, you placed foreigners in charge of my sanctuary."'
26Ezk 44:9 "This is what the Lord God says, 'No foreigner who is both uncircumcised in heart and flesh, of all the foreigners who are among the Israelites is to enter my sanctuary.
26Ezk 44:10 But the Levites, who went far away from me when Israel abandoned me, who left me to follow their idols, are to bear the punishment of their iniquity.
26Ezk 44:11 Nevertheless, they are to serve in my sanctuary, overseeing the gates of the temple, ministering to the temple, slaughtering the burnt offerings and the sacrifices presented for the people, standing in the presence of the people, and ministering to them.
26Ezk 44:12 Because they kept serving them in the presence of their idols, becoming a sin-filled stumbling block to the house of Israel,'" declares the Lord God. "'I have sworn against them that they are to bear the consequences of their iniquity.
26Ezk 44:13 They are not to come near me to serve as a priest to me, nor approach any of my holy things, including the most holy things. Instead, they are to bear the shame of the loathsome things that they have committed.
26Ezk 44:14 Nevertheless, I will appoint them to take care of my temple, includings all of its service and everything that is to be done inside of it.'"
26Ezk 44:15 "The descendants of Zadok, Levitical priests who took care of my sanctuary when the Israelites wandered away from me, are to come near me to minister to me. They are to stand before me to offer the fat and the blood to me," declares the Lord God.
26Ezk 44:16 "They are to enter my sanctuary, approach my table to minister to me, and observe my requirements.
26Ezk 44:17 Whenever they enter at the gates of the inner court, they are to be clothed with linen garments. They are not to wear wool when they are ministering within the gates of the inner courtyard or in the temple.
26Ezk 44:18 Linen turbans are to be on their heads, and they are to wear linen undergarments. Also, they are not to clothe themselves with anything that makes them perspire.
26Ezk 44:19 "When they enter the outer courtyard, that is, the outer courtyard where the people are, they are to take off their garments in which they were ministering, lay them in the consecrated chambers, and put on different garments so they will not transfer holiness to the people through their garments.
