26Ezk 44:21 "None of the priests are to drink wine upon entering the inner courtyard.
26Ezk 44:22 "They are not to marry a widow or a divorced woman. Instead, they are to marry virgins from the descendants of the house of Israel, or a widow who is the widow of a priest."
26Ezk 44:23 "They are to teach my people how to discern what is holy compared to what is common, showing them how to discern between what is unclean and clean.
26Ezk 44:24 When disputes arise, they are to take their stand to judge, adjudicating matters according to my ordinances. They are to enforce my laws, my statutes, all of my appointed feasts, and they are to sanctify my Sabbaths.
26Ezk 44:25 "They are not to come in contact with a dead body, so as not to defile themselves, except in the case of their father, mother, son, daughter, brother, or for an unmarried sister, on whose behalf they may defile themselves.
26Ezk 44:26 After he is cleansed, he is to remain exempt from ministry for seven days.
26Ezk 44:27 On the day that he returns to the sanctuary's inner court to minister, he is to offer his own sin offering," declares the Lord God.
26Ezk 44:28 "Now with respect to their inheritances, I am to be their inheritance, and you are to give them no possession in Israel, since I am their possession.
26Ezk 44:29 They are to eat the grain offerings, sin offering, and guilt offering. Everything consecrated in Israel is to belong to them.
26Ezk 44:30 The first portion of all the first fruits of every kind and every offering of any kind is to be for the priests. You are to give the priest the first portion of your grain. As a result a blessing will rest on your household.
26Ezk 44:31 However, the priests are not to eat any bird or animal that has died a natural death or that has been torn apart."
26Ezk 45:1 "When you divide the land for an inheritance, you are to present a Terumah to the Lord, a consecrated portion of the land, the length of which is to be 25,000 cubits, and the width of which is to be 20,000 cubits. The entire contents of this area are to be treated as holy."
