26Ezk 45:13 "Here are the standards for presenting offerings£º a sixth of an ephah that is based on the standard homer of wheat, and a sixth of an ephah based on the standard homer of barley.
26Ezk 45:14 The olive oil quota is to be based on the bath, measured at ten baths to each homer, which is equal to one kor.
26Ezk 45:15 The sheep quota is to be one from each flock of 200 taken from the pastures of Israel. From all of these you are to present grain offerings, burnt offerings, and peace offerings, to make atonement for them," declares the Lord God.
26Ezk 45:16 "The entire nation living in the land is to present this offering to the Regent Prince in Israel.
26Ezk 45:17 The Regent Prince is to provide the burnt offerings, grain offerings, and drink offerings at the feasts, on the new moons and Sabbaths, and at all of the proscribed feasts of the house of Israel. He is to provide the grain offerings, burnt offerings, and peace offerings in order to make atonement for the house of Israel."
26Ezk 45:18 "This is what the Lord God says, 'On the first day of the first month, you are to present a young bull without defect in order to cleanse the sanctuary.
26Ezk 45:19 The priest is to place some of the blood from the sin offering on the door posts of the temple, on the four corners of the ledge around the altar, and on the posts of the gate leading to the inner court.
26Ezk 45:20 You are also to do this on the seventh day of the month, to make atonement for any person who wanders away or who sins through ignorance in order to make atonement for the temple.
26Ezk 45:21 "'On the fourteenth day of the first month, you are to observe the Passover as a feast for seven days. Unleavened bread is to be eaten.
26Ezk 45:22 On that day, the Regent Prince is to provide, both for himself and for all the people who live in the land, a bull for a sin offering.
26Ezk 45:23 Each day during the seven days of the feast, he is to provide a burnt offering to the Lord, consisting of seven bulls and seven rams without defect, offered each day throughout the seven days, along with a male goat offered each day as a sin offering.
