28Hs 4:8 They feed on the sin of my people; they purpose in their heart to transgress.
28Hs 4:9 So it will be£º like people, like priest. I will punish them for their lifestyles, rewarding them according to their behavior.
28Hs 4:10 They will eat, but will not be satisfied. They will engage in prostitution, but they won't increase, because they have stopped listening to the Lord.
28Hs 4:11 "Sexual immorality, wine, and fresh wine seduce the heart of my people.
28Hs 4:12 My people seek counsel from their piece of wood, and their diviner's rod speaks to them. For a spirit of prostitution causes them to go astray; in their immorality they desert their God.
28Hs 4:13 They offer sacrifices on the mountain tops, burning offerings on the hills, under oaks, poplars, and terebinth trees, since their shade is very good. Therefore your daughters are prostitutes and your daughters-in-law commit adultery. 
28Hs 4:14 However, I'm not going to punish your daughters when they commit prostitution, nor your daughters-in-law when they commit adultery, because their men are themselves immoral?they offer sacrifices with prostitutes. These people who aren't discerning will stumble.
28Hs 4:15 "Even though you prostitute yourself, Israel?let not Judah incur guilt?don't go to Gilgal, or visit Beth-aven, or swear an oath using the Lord's name.
28Hs 4:16 For Israel is as obstinate as a stubborn mule! Nevertheless, will not the Lord feed them like a lamb in a broad pasture - 
28Hs 4:17 Ephraim has become entwined with idols; leave him alone!
28Hs 4:18 While drinking to excess, they prostitute themselves. They're in love with dishonor.
28Hs 4:19 A wind storm will carry them away in its embrace, and their sacrifices will bring them shame."
28Hs 5:1 "Hear this, priests, pay attention, house of Israel, listen, royal family! For judgment is coming your way, because you have been a trap to Mizpah, a snare spread out on Mount Tabor.
28Hs 5:2 The rebels are deep into their slaughter; I am punishing them all.
28Hs 5:3 I know Ephraim, and Israel cannot hide from me, since you, Ephraim, have been acting like a prostitute, defiling Israel.
28Hs 5:4 "Their actions hinder them from turning to their God, because a spirit of fornication is in their midst, and the Lord they do not know.
28Hs 5:5 The arrogance of Israel testifies against him; therefore Israel and Ephraim will stumble in their iniquity, and Judah with them.
28Hs 5:6 They will go with their flocks and herds to seek the Lord, but they will not find him; he has withdrawn from them.
28Hs 5:7 They have been unfaithful to the Lord, having raised unbelieving children. In the coming month they will be devoured, along with their fields.
28Hs 5:8 "Sound the trumpet in Gibeah, and the alarm in Ramah. Cry out at Beth-aven Go out, Benjamin!
28Hs 5:9 Ephraim will be desolate when it is rebuked. I have made known among the tribes of Israel what will surely come about.
28Hs 5:10 The princes of Judah have become like those who move boundary markers£º I will pour out my anger on them like water.
28Hs 5:11 Ephraim is crushed, broken by judgment, because he willingly pursued idols.
28Hs 5:12 Therefore I will consume Ephraim like a moth, and the house of Judah as rottenness consumes.
28Hs 5:13 When Ephraim examined his illness and Judah his injury, then Ephraim went to Assyria, and inquired of the great king; but he could not cure you nor heal your injury.
28Hs 5:14 Therefore I will be like a lion to Ephraim, and like a young lion to the house of Judah. I?even I?will tear them to pieces, and then I will leave. I will take them away, and there will be no rescue.
28Hs 5:15 "I will leave and go back to my place until they admit their offense and seek my face. When affliction comes to them, they will eagerly seek me."
28Hs 6:1 "Come, let us return to the Lord; even though he has torn us, he will heal us. Even though he has wounded us, he will bind our wounds.
28Hs 6:2 After two days he will restore us to life, on the third day he will raise us up, and we will live in his presence.
28Hs 6:3 Let us know, let us pursue knowledge of the Lord; his coming is as certain as the dawn. He will come to us like the rain, like the autumn and spring rains come on the earth.
28Hs 6:4 "What am I to do with you, Ephraim?What am I to do with you, Judah?Your love is like a morning rain cloud?it passes away like the morning dew.
