28Hs 6:6 For it is love that I seek, and not sacrifice; knowledge of God more than burnt offerings.
28Hs 6:7 "But like Adam, they broke the covenant; in this they have acted deceitfully against me.
28Hs 6:8 Gilead is a lawless town; it is polluted by bloodshed.
28Hs 6:9 Like a gang of thieves that stalk a man, priests commit murder along the road to Shechem, committing shameful crimes.
28Hs 6:10 I have seen a horrible evil in the house of Israel?Ephraim's promiscuity. Israel is defiled.
28Hs 6:11 "So, Judah, a harvest has been appointed for you when I restore my people from captivity."
28Hs 7:1 "When I was healing Israel, Ephraim's sin was uncovered, along with Samaria's wickedness. While they craft lying schemes, the thief invades, and the gang of thieves plunders outside.
28Hs 7:2 It never occurs to them that I remember all their sin. Now their actions have caught up with them, and they have my attention.
28Hs 7:3 They please the king with their evil, and the princes with their dishonesty.
28Hs 7:4 All of them are adulterers?they burn like an oven prepared by the baker, who has ceased stoking it until the dough is leavened.
28Hs 7:5 "On the king's festival day the princes got drunk from wine, so the king joined the mockers.
28Hs 7:6 For they have stirred up themselves like an oven as they lie in ambush. Their baker sleeps through the night; in the morning, the oven will be blazing like a fire.
28Hs 7:7 They all burn like an oven; they have consumed their judges; all their kings have fallen?not even one of them calls on me.
28Hs 7:8 "Ephraim compromises with the nations; he's a half-baked cake.
28Hs 7:9 Foreigners have consumed his strength, and he hasn't noticed. Furthermore, his head is sprinkled with gray hair, but he doesn't realize it.
28Hs 7:10 Israel's arrogance testifies against him; but they do not return to the Lord their God, nor seek him in all of this.
28Hs 7:11 "Ephraim is also like a silly dove, lacking sense£º They call out to Egypt, and turn toward Assyria.
28Hs 7:12 When they go, I'll cast my net over them. I'll bring them down, as one shoots birds in the sky. I'll chasten them, as the assembly has already heard.
28Hs 7:13 Woe to them?because they have run away from me. Ruin to them?because they have sinned against me. Even though I redeemed them, they spread lies against me.
28Hs 7:14 They will not cry to me from their heart?instead, they wail on their beds. They gather together to eat and drink, turning away from me.
28Hs 7:15 "Though I have taught them and strengthened their arms, nevertheless they plot evil against me.
28Hs 7:16 They return?but not to the Most High. They are like a defective weapon. Their princes will fall by the sword because of their raging tongue, and they will be a laughingstock in the land of Egypt."
28Hs 8:1 "Sound the ram's horn! Like a vulture the enemy will come against the temple of the Lord, because Israel violated my covenant, transgressing my law.
28Hs 8:2 They cry out to me, 'God, we of Israel acknowledge you.'
28Hs 8:3 "Israel has discarded what is good. The enemy will pursue them.
